    Veterinary Clinics in Bangalore

    (12368 Ratings & Reviews) 4.2 Average Ratings

    Veterinary Clinics in Bangalore

    Providing excellent grooming and health care for your animals are the veterinary clinics that are all around the city. These centers are known to primarily offer all kinds of medical assistance to domestic animals. Experienced as well as highly passionate about animal care, are the doctors and the other medical assistants housed at each of these centers. Other than diagnosing and providing treatment to these animals, many of these pet facilities also offer a range of grooming services. Classified among the most commonly requested for grooming services are clipping of nails, cleaning of ears, bathing of the animals, trimming of fur and cleaning of teeth. It is of utmost importance to have your domestic pets vaccinated when being brought into the home and on a regular basis thereafter. Apart from grooming and medical services, many of these places also give you the option of shopping for all kinds of food, accessories and toys for your pet. Kindly scroll to the top and search for the best veterinary clinics in Bangalore.

    Frequently Asked Questions

    1. Are veterinary clinics in Bangalore equipped to perform surgeries on animals/ pets?

    Yes, a select few places have the required infrastructure for surgeries. They have trained veterinary surgeons on board who perform a variety of routine surgeries.

    2. Do I have to book an appointment before visiting the veterinary clinics in Bangalore?

    No, not all clinics require you to book an appointment. It is better to call and ask whether you have to.

    3. Do pet clinics also offer lodging/boarding services?

    Only a few clinics are known to provide lodging and boarding facilities. Kindly check with the pet clinic in question.

    4. Do pet clinics in Bangalore provide ambulance services in case of emergencies?

    Some clinics have their own ambulances and some have tie-ups with pet ambulance providers to transport pets to the clinic in emergency cases.

    5. Do clinics carry out blood tests and other medical procedures?

    Most clinics are equipped to perform blood tests and other procedures. However, please check before booking an appointment.
